[Smaller hand drum = kouuteseinoe'ehi because used when ceremony where women take off shawls to dance thus the name for the district - they would camp there on the way to rations at Ft. Washakie, and would pass time by playing small hand drum together. Ho'yei - small drum used in sun dance]
